  "step_by_step_reasoning": "The transcript describes a serverless AI-driven meeting summarization architecture from Granicus. 1. The flow starts with Meeting Applications sending requests to API Gateway, which forwards them to an Ingest Lambda. 2. The Ingest Lambda saves meeting metadata in DynamoDB and transcript files in S3. 3. S3 transcript creation triggers a Step Functions workflow. 4. Within Step Functions, a Map parallel state runs a Summarization Lambda across agenda items in parallel, utilizing Bedrock (Claude 3) to summarize segments. 5. Once done, an Aggregation Lambda runs to combine the segments into a final document stored in a separate S3 Summaries bucket, and updates status in DynamoDB. 6. Users fetch results through API Gateway via a Retrieval Lambda, which reads from DynamoDB and S3.",
